Ideally, what I would want is a `fatalAssert` method (or something similar) that ends the test suite when its input is an error. Something that would perhaps be called `fatalAssertNotError`, but I don&#39;t think that exists. If it did, the last line of my first function would simply be `testCase.fatalAssertNotError(connfun(connloc))` and I would not have to worry about all the cases.

